[30;1m32 | [0m[35m#. Identify the chunk of code for rehoming. Applicable code includes common[0m
[30;1m33 | [0m[35m   classes/functions/modules/etc. that are consumed by networking project(s) outside of[0m
[30;1m34 | [0m[35m   neutron. Optimal consumption patterns of the code at hand must also be considered to[0m
[30;1m35 | [0m[35m   ensure the rehomed code addresses any technical debt. Finally, leave low-hanging[0m
[30;1m36 | [0m[35m   fruit for last and tackle the most commonly used code first. If you have any doubt[0m
[30;1m37 | [0m[35m   about the applicability of code for rehoming, reach out to one of the neutron core[0m

[30;1m71 | [0m[35mParticularly, a value of ``ATTR_NOT_SPECIFIED`` is different from an[0m
[30;1m72 | [0m[35mattribute that has been specified with a value of ``None``.  For example,[0m
[30;1m73 | [0m[35mif ``gateway_ip`` is omitted in a request to create a subnet, the plugin[0m
[30;1m74 | [0m[35mwill receive ``ATTR_NOT_SPECIFIED`` and the default gateway IP will be[0m
[30;1m75 | [0m[35mgenerated.  However, if ``gateway_ip`` is specified as ``None``, this means[0m
[30;1m76 | [0m[35mthat the subnet does not have a gateway IP.[0m

[30;1m509 | [0m[35mWhat is the relationship between Callbacks and Taskflow?[0m
[30;1m510 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m511 | [0m[35m   There is no overlap between Callbacks and Taskflow or mutual exclusion; as matter of fact they[0m
[30;1m512 | [0m[35m   can be combined; You could have a callback that goes on and trigger a taskflow. It is a nice[0m
[30;1m513 | [0m[35m   way of separating implementation from abstraction, because you can keep the callback in place[0m
[30;1m514 | [0m[35m   and change Taskflow with something else.[0m

[30;1m43 | [0m[35mNeutron core. A callback system, and its registry, tries to address these issues.[0m
[30;1m44 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m45 | [0m[35mIn object-oriented software systems, method invocation is also known as message[0m
[30;1m46 | [0m[35mpassing: an object passes a message to another object, and it may or may not expect[0m
[30;1m47 | [0m[35ma message back. This point-to-point interaction can take place between the parties[0m
[30;1m48 | [0m[35mdirectly involved in the communication, or it can happen via an intermediary. The[0m
[30;1m49 | [0m[35mintermediary is then in charge of keeping track of who is interested in the messages[0m
[30;1m50 | [0m[35mand in delivering the messages forth and back, when required. As mentioned earlier,[0m

[30;1m9 | [0m[35m    end at the end of a reader/writer context. In this case, a session could[0m

[30;1m11 | [0m[35m    context. In order to mimic the previous behaviour, this method checks[0m
[30;1m12 | [0m[35m    the pending new, deleted and dirty elements to be flushed. In case of[0m

[30;1m113 | [0m[35m    servers are more frequently the cause of timeouts rather than lost[0m
[30;1m114 | [0m[35m    messages.[0m
[30;1m115 | [0m[35m    """[0m

[30;1m4 | [0m[35m    Add the API extension ``uplink-status-propagation-updatable`` to make the[0m
[30;1m5 | [0m[35m    port field ``propagate_uplink_status`` updatable. Now it is possible to send[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35m    a port PUT request to update the value defined during the creation. This[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35m    change will have an effect in the ML2/SR-IOV agent that will need to update[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35m    the VF status accordingly.[0m
